    "title": "Now Hiring Medical Officer at Abbott India Holdings Services",
    "description": "Abbott India Holdings Services is actively seeking a talented and motivated Medical Officer to join our dynamic team in Patna. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Abbott India Holdings Services:\nAbbott India Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Flexible working hours\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Patna, Bihar, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Abbott India Holdings Services!",
